    "summary": "Carla G. Silva\n8, Quai Edouard Van Beneden\n4020 Li\u00e8ge, Belgium Cell: +32(0)471667377\ncgomesdasilva@uliege.be\n\nI am a neuroscientist interested in understanding how the brain is generated and develops. I am particularly interested in understanding the non-canonical role of migrating cells during brain development. While the brain is developing, cells may display distinct roles from the ones the \u201cclassical\u201d functions. For example, I discovered that interneurons, the inhibitory cells of the brain, are able to influence cortical development by scaling cortical progenitor proliferation. I am now interested in exploring the role of oligodendrocyte precursor cells during brain maturation and wiring.\n\nEDUCATION\n\u25aa\tUniversity of Coimbra \u2013 Degree in Biology (Average:17 over 20) - 2006\n\u25aa\tPhD from University of Coimbra \u2013 Thesis Title: Effect of Purines in the Developing Hippocampus \u2013 Consequences for the Establishment of Circuits Related to Learning and Memory - 2011\n\u25aa\tPost-doctoral training \u2013 GIGA Stem Cells, Li\u00e8ge, Belgium; Laboratory of Molecular Regulation of Neurogenesis \u2013 2012 until present\n\n\n",
